args: Oh, I tried to stay away. But these little\ninsects kept comin' at me, so what's a\ngirl to do?
Figured I'd just come destroy their nest\nand be done with it.
You liken us to insects, yet I have lured\nyou here like a moth to flame!
It's barely been any time at all since my\nslipup broke your little toy.
Yet here you are, ready and waiting with\nan army of troops...\nYou're far too prepared.
You knew this was how things were gonna\nplay out, didn't you?
...You've been waiting for a chance to get\nrid of me for some time.
At least tell it to me straight!\nEnough with the subterfuge!

This is what it means to be part of a group.
Someone like you, with your mistaken
idea of freedom, will likely never
understand.
And I'm done talking!\nMake them hurt, Renegade Queen!
My, my. The damage has reached the\nanticipated value. Bring out Ij-459.
I am well aware we can't control it.\nThe alternative, however, is our\ndemise—or are you a traitor too?
Ij-459 has been infused with even greater\nlevels of draconic mana than the late\nIj-458. Do you know what that means?
It's another failure you can't control?

What it lacks in controllability, it makes up
for in strength and belligerence. If you
consider strength to be the measure of
freedom, then it is clearly freer than you!
I-it's going to kill us all!
Is feeding your cravings at will not your\nvery definition of freedom?
You seek to act however you wish, free of\nall ties—but there is no value in that.
No, the true value of freedom is found in\nsubjugation. The awareness of what binds\nyou, and the strength to overcome it.

Until you are able to understand that,
you will continue to be but a petulant
child, indulging in tantrums.
Just like Ij-459 here.
Well, I believe this is where we part ways.
You're just gonna leave your toy behind?
...You accused me earlier of planning to\nbe rid of you, yes? Well, you were only\nhalf right.
I didn't just want to eliminate you,\nIj-9—I wanted to destroy the entire\nIj series. The project as a whole.
What...? If you were planning on killing\nthis thing to begin with, why even make\nit?! Cut the crap!
Your opinion is of no consequence.\nThe truth of the matter is there is\nno future for the Ij series.
The fact that, after 450 subjects, none have\nsurpassed the now-ancient Ij-9 is proof\nenough.
What? I thought you said Ij-458's scores\ntotally dwarfed mine?
The scores meant little. I merely needed\nsomething to placate the Syndicate's\ndemands for evidence of progress.
So you were full of it from the start...\nAnd now you need a way to shut this\nhideout down too, right?
A project this well-funded cannot be so\neasily dismantled, after all.
Oh, it's a big job all right.\nAnd I'm just another cog in the works.

Heh. Catching on, are you? That's right.
I knew you would turn traitor. It was
the last element I needed to pull
my plan together.

The Syndicate abhors traitors above all
else. So when I sacrifice my subordinates
and base to kill this particularly dangerous
one? Why, they'll thank me.
What—no! You're seriously okay with\nkilling all these people?!
Hah. It's rather rich to hear that from\nsuch a prolific killer as yourself.
I am but a lowly farmer whose fields no\nlonger come to harvest. What else is there\nto do but leave for greener pastures?
And so, I take what I can from my\nold field, to help me on my way.\nIs that not the natural course?
Maybe. But I don't think things are gonna\ngo to plan.
You would stop me, would you?\nEven now you fail to see your\nfreedom is at my behest.
You are our puppet, Ij-9.\nYou have never been free.
...Maybe you're right. But that doesn't\nmean I can't win my freedom now.
Hah! You have spunk, if nothing else.\nBut alas, my dear, Ij-459 is far stronger\nthan you.
Not much of a talker, huh?\nWell, you ARE a newborn, I guess.
All right, Renegade Queen, let's show this\nkid who's the strongest around here!
